If you find yourself stuck in SINGLE_USER mode in a SQL Server database, do the following:
1 - Find SPIDs connected to your database USE master GO EXEC sp_who Note any SPIDs connected to your database, and then&hellip;
2 - Kill connections KILL [spid] -- do this for each spid returned by exec sp_who 3 - Set back to MULTI_USER USE Master ALTER DATABASE DatabaseName SET MULTI_USER Plan B (If that doesn&rsquo;t work) If that doesn&rsquo;t work, the following query can be used to find the connection(s):
